cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SI

This paper deals with the classification of Android malware signatures using machine learning techniques and community detection algorithms. It involves the analysis of large datasets and the development of a structural equation model to identify the most powerful Anti-Virus engines for detecting different types of malware. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are: 

- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): This sub-category deals with the study of security protocols, cryptographic algorithms, and threat analysis, which are all relevant to the topic of malware detection and classification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers the use of machine learning and data mining techniques for solving complex problems, which is the main focus of this paper. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is closely related to cs.AI and deals specifically with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): This sub-category deals with the development of software systems and the management of software projects, which are relevant to the implementation and deployment of Anti-Virus engines. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category deals with the analysis of large-scale networks and the development of algorithms for community detection, which are used in this paper to identify similarities between malware classes.
